    <item>
      <title>verb</title>
      <link>https://trtrf.github.io/tense/verb/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://trtrf.github.io/tense/verb/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt; is a word that expresses &lt;strong&gt;action&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;state of being&lt;/strong&gt;. It tells us what the subject of a sentence is doing or experiencing.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;principal-verbs&#34;&gt;Principal Verbs&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Principal verbs are the main verbs in a sentence, and they are used to express an action, state, or occurrence. There are two types of principal verbs:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;主要动词&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;transitive-ˈtrænsətɪv&#34;&gt;transitive /ˈtræn.sə.tɪv/&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Transitive verbs are verbs that require an object to complete their meaning.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;vt:see,watch,hear,notice&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
